   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Handling Class Imbalance\n",
    "\n",
    "With only 0.17% fraud, a model that predicts *everything* as legitimate would achieve 99.83% accuracy — but catch zero fraud. That's useless in practice.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Strategy: Undersampling** — we reduce the majority class (legitimate) to match the minority class (fraud) in the training set. This forces the model to learn fraud patterns properly.\n",
    "\n",
    "> In production, you'd also consider SMOTE (synthetic oversampling) or class weights. We'll use class weights in the model too as a comparison."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
